✅ Real World Tasks of a Junior DevOps Engineer
Below are the actual tasks companies assign to freshers/juniors.

🔹 1. Deploy Applications
You’ll often deploy apps on:
	• AWS EC2
	• Docker
	• Kubernetes
	• ECS / EKS
	• On-prem servers
Typical tickets:
	• “Deploy the new Node.js build on dev server.”
	• “Update Docker image to version v1.2.4.”
	• “App running on EC2 is down — restart & check logs.”

🔹 2. CI/CD Pipelines
You must manage or fix CI/CD pipelines in:
	• GitHub Actions
	• GitLab CI
	• Jenkins
	• Bitbucket Pipelines
Sample tickets:
	• “Pipeline failing in build stage. Fix it.”
	• “Add S3 upload step after build.”
	• “Add dev → staging → prod pipeline approvals.”

🔹 3. Linux Administration
90% of DevOps work is on Linux.
You must know:
	• SSH
	• Systemctl (start/stop services)
	• Logs /var/log/*
	• Cron jobs
	• Disk, network, CPU commands
Tickets:
	• “Server out of disk — cleanup /var/log.”
	• “Nginx service down — troubleshoot.”
	• “Increase ulimit for Node app.”

🔹 4. AWS Tasks
You will frequently work with:
	• EC2
	• S3
	• IAM
	• VPC
	• CloudWatch
	• Load Balancers
Real tickets:
	• “Create IAM user with S3-only access.”
	• “EC2 CPU high — find the cause.”
	• “Configure ALB to forward traffic to new backend.”

🔹 5. Infrastructure-as-Code (IaC)
Using Terraform or CloudFormation to create:
	• VPC
	• Subnets
	• EC2
	• Security groups
	• RDS
	• ASG
	• S3 buckets
Tickets:
	• “Write Terraform for EC2 + security group.”
	• “Update ASG launch template.”
	• “Fix Terraform drift (terraform plan mismatch).”

🔹 6. Containers (Docker + Kubernetes)
You must understand:
	• Dockerfile
	• Docker Compose
	• Kubernetes YAMLs
	• Deployments, Services, Ingress
	• ConfigMap, Secret
	• HPA, VPA
Tickets:
	• “Fix imagePullBackOff in POD.”
	• “Increase replica count to 4.”
	• “Add liveness probe to backend deployment.”

🔹 7. Monitoring / Alerts
Tools:
	• Prometheus + Grafana
	• CloudWatch
	• ELK
	• Datadog
Tickets:
	• “Add alert for 80% CPU usage.”
	• “Create dashboard for EC2 metrics.”
	• “Fix broken Prometheus scrape config.”

